201 void AArch64AsmPrinter::emitStartOfAsmFile(Module &M) { 0
202 const Triple &TT = TM.getTargetTriple(); 0
203 ----
204 if (TT.isOSBinFormatCOFF()) { 0
205 // Emit an absolute @feat.00 symbol ----
206 MCSymbol *S = MMI->getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(StringRef("@feat.00")); 0
207 OutStreamer->beginCOFFSymbolDef(S); 0
208 OutStreamer->emitCOFFSymbolStorageClass(COFF::IMAGE_SYM_CLASS_STATIC); 0
209 OutStreamer->emitCOFFSymbolType(COFF::IMAGE_SYM_DTYPE_NULL); 0
210 OutStreamer->endCOFFSymbolDef(); 0
211 int64_t Feat00Value = 0; 0
212 ----
213 if (M.getModuleFlag("cfguard")) { 0
214 // Object is CFG-aware. ----
215 Feat00Value |= COFF::Feat00Flags::GuardCF; 0
216 } ----
217 ----
218 if (M.getModuleFlag("ehcontguard")) { 0
219 // Object also has EHCont. ----
220 Feat00Value |= COFF::Feat00Flags::GuardEHCont; 0
221 } ----
222 ----
223 if (M.getModuleFlag("ms-kernel")) { 0
224 // Object is compiled with /kernel. ----
225 Feat00Value |= COFF::Feat00Flags::Kernel; 0
226 } ----
227 ----
228 OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(S, MCSA_Global); 0
229 OutStreamer->emitAssignment( 0
230 S, MCConstantExpr::create(Feat00Value, MMI->getContext())); 0
231 } ----
232 ----
233 if (!TT.isOSBinFormatELF()) 0
234 return; 0
235 ----
236 // Assemble feature flags that may require creation of a note section. ----
237 unsigned Flags = 0; 0
238 if (const auto *BTE = mdconst::extract_or_null( 0
239 M.getModuleFlag("branch-target-enforcement"))) 0
240 if (BTE->getZExtValue()) 0
241 Flags |= ELF::GNU_PROPERTY_AARCH64_FEATURE_1_BTI; 0
242 ----
243 if (const auto *Sign = mdconst::extract_or_null( 0
244 M.getModuleFlag("sign-return-address"))) 0
245 if (Sign->getZExtValue()) 0
246 Flags |= ELF::GNU_PROPERTY_AARCH64_FEATURE_1_PAC; 0
247 ----
248 if (Flags == 0) 0
249 return; 0
250 ----
251 // Emit a .note.gnu.property section with the flags. ----
252 auto *TS = ----
253 static_cast(OutStreamer->getTargetStreamer()); 0
254 TS->emitNoteSection(Flags); 0
255 } ----

288 void AArch64AsmPrinter::emitSled(const MachineInstr &MI, SledKind Kind) { 0
289 static const int8_t NoopsInSledCount = 7; ----
290 // We want to emit the following pattern: ----
291 // ----
292 // .Lxray_sled_N: ----
293 // ALIGN ----
294 // B #32 ----
295 // ; 7 NOP instructions (28 bytes) ----
296 // .tmpN ----
297 // ----
298 // We need the 28 bytes (7 instructions) because at runtime, we'd be patching ----
299 // over the full 32 bytes (8 instructions) with the following pattern: ----
300 // ----
301 // STP X0, X30, [SP, #-16]! ; push X0 and the link register to the stack ----
302 // LDR W17, #12 ; W17 := function ID ----
303 // LDR X16,#12 ; X16 := addr of __xray_FunctionEntry or __xray_FunctionExit ----
304 // BLR X16 ; call the tracing trampoline ----
305 // ;DATA: 32 bits of function ID ----
306 // ;DATA: lower 32 bits of the address of the trampoline ----
307 // ;DATA: higher 32 bits of the address of the trampoline ----
308 // LDP X0, X30, [SP], #16 ; pop X0 and the link register from the stack ----
309 // ----
310 OutStreamer->emitCodeAlignment(Align(4), &getSubtargetInfo()); 0
311 auto CurSled = OutContext.createTempSymbol("xray_sled_", true); 0
312 OutStreamer->emitLabel(CurSled); 0
313 auto Target = OutContext.createTempSymbol(); 0
314 ----
315 // Emit "B #32" instruction, which jumps over the next 28 bytes. ----
316 // The operand has to be the number of 4-byte instructions to jump over, ----
317 // including the current instruction. ----
318 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::B).addImm(8)); 0
319 ----
320 for (int8_t I = 0; I < NoopsInSledCount; I++) 0
321 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::HINT).addImm(0)); 0
322 ----
323 OutStreamer->emitLabel(Target); 0
324 recordSled(CurSled, MI, Kind, 2); 0
325 } 0
326 ----
327 // Emit the following code for Intrinsic::{xray_customevent,xray_typedevent} ----
328 // (built-in functions __xray_customevent/__xray_typedevent). ----
329 // ----
330 // .Lxray_event_sled_N: ----
331 // b 1f ----
332 // save x0 and x1 (and also x2 for TYPED_EVENT_CALL) ----
333 // set up x0 and x1 (and also x2 for TYPED_EVENT_CALL) ----
334 // bl __xray_CustomEvent or __xray_TypedEvent ----
335 // restore x0 and x1 (and also x2 for TYPED_EVENT_CALL) ----
336 // 1: ----
337 // ----
338 // There are 6 instructions for EVENT_CALL and 9 for TYPED_EVENT_CALL. ----
339 // ----
340 // Then record a sled of kind CUSTOM_EVENT or TYPED_EVENT. ----
341 // After patching, b .+N will become a nop. ----
342 void AArch64AsmPrinter::LowerPATCHABLE_EVENT_CALL(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
343 bool Typed) { ----
344 auto &O = *OutStreamer; 0
345 MCSymbol *CurSled = OutContext.createTempSymbol("xray_sled_", true); 0
346 O.emitLabel(CurSled); 0
347 MCInst MovX0Op0 = MCInstBuilder(AArch64::ORRXrs) 0
348 .addReg(AArch64::X0) 0
349 .addReg(AArch64::XZR) 0
350 .addReg(MI.getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
351 .addImm(0); 0
352 MCInst MovX1Op1 = MCInstBuilder(AArch64::ORRXrs) 0
353 .addReg(AArch64::X1) 0
354 .addReg(AArch64::XZR) 0
355 .addReg(MI.getOperand(1).getReg()) 0
356 .addImm(0); 0
357 bool MachO = TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO(); 0
358 auto *Sym = MCSymbolRefExpr::create( 0
359 OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol( 0
360 Twine(MachO ? "_" : "") + 0
361 (Typed ? "__xray_TypedEvent" : "__xray_CustomEvent")), 0
362 OutContext); ----
363 if (Typed) { 0
364 O.AddComment("Begin XRay typed event"); 0
365 EmitToStreamer(O, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::B).addImm(9)); 0
366 EmitToStreamer(O, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::STPXpre) 0
367 .addReg(AArch64::SP) 0
368 .addReg(AArch64::X0) 0
369 .addReg(AArch64::X1) 0
370 .addReg(AArch64::SP) 0
371 .addImm(-4)); 0
372 EmitToStreamer(O, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::STRXui) 0
373 .addReg(AArch64::X2) 0
374 .addReg(AArch64::SP) 0
375 .addImm(2)); 0
376 EmitToStreamer(O, MovX0Op0); 0
377 EmitToStreamer(O, MovX1Op1); 0
378 EmitToStreamer(O, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::ORRXrs) 0
379 .addReg(AArch64::X2) 0
380 .addReg(AArch64::XZR) 0
381 .addReg(MI.getOperand(2).getReg()) 0
382 .addImm(0)); 0
383 EmitToStreamer(O, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::BL).addExpr(Sym)); 0
384 EmitToStreamer(O, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::LDRXui) 0
385 .addReg(AArch64::X2) 0
386 .addReg(AArch64::SP) 0
387 .addImm(2)); 0
388 O.AddComment("End XRay typed event"); 0
389 EmitToStreamer(O, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::LDPXpost) 0
390 .addReg(AArch64::SP) 0
391 .addReg(AArch64::X0) 0
392 .addReg(AArch64::X1) 0
393 .addReg(AArch64::SP) 0
394 .addImm(4)); 0
395 ----
396 recordSled(CurSled, MI, SledKind::TYPED_EVENT, 2); 0
397 } else { ----
398 O.AddComment("Begin XRay custom event"); 0
399 EmitToStreamer(O, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::B).addImm(6)); 0
400 EmitToStreamer(O, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::STPXpre) 0
401 .addReg(AArch64::SP) 0
402 .addReg(AArch64::X0) 0
403 .addReg(AArch64::X1) 0
404 .addReg(AArch64::SP) 0
405 .addImm(-2)); 0
406 EmitToStreamer(O, MovX0Op0); 0
407 EmitToStreamer(O, MovX1Op1); 0
408 EmitToStreamer(O, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::BL).addExpr(Sym)); 0
409 O.AddComment("End XRay custom event"); 0
410 EmitToStreamer(O, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::LDPXpost) 0
411 .addReg(AArch64::SP) 0
412 .addReg(AArch64::X0) 0
413 .addReg(AArch64::X1) 0
414 .addReg(AArch64::SP) 0
415 .addImm(2)); 0
416 ----
417 recordSled(CurSled, MI, SledKind::CUSTOM_EVENT, 2); 0
418 } ----
419 } 0

421 void AArch64AsmPrinter::LowerKCFI_CHECK(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
422 Register AddrReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
423 assert(std::next(MI.getIterator())->isCall() && 0
424 "KCFI_CHECK not followed by a call instruction"); ----
425 assert(std::next(MI.getIterator())->getOperand(0).getReg() == AddrReg && 0
426 "KCFI_CHECK call target doesn't match call operand"); ----
427 ----
428 // Default to using the intra-procedure-call temporary registers for ----
429 // comparing the hashes. ----
430 unsigned ScratchRegs[] = {AArch64::W16, AArch64::W17}; 0
431 if (AddrReg == AArch64::XZR) { 0
432 // Checking XZR makes no sense. Instead of emitting a load, zero ----
433 // ScratchRegs[0] and use it for the ESR AddrIndex below. ----
434 AddrReg = getXRegFromWReg(ScratchRegs[0]); 0
435 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::ORRXrs) 0
436 .addReg(AddrReg) 0
437 .addReg(AArch64::XZR) 0
438 .addReg(AArch64::XZR) 0
439 .addImm(0)); 0
440 } else { ----
441 // If one of the scratch registers is used for the call target (e.g. ----
442 // with AArch64::TCRETURNriBTI), we can clobber another caller-saved ----
443 // temporary register instead (in this case, AArch64::W9) as the check ----
444 // is immediately followed by the call instruction. ----
445 for (auto &Reg : ScratchRegs) { 0
446 if (Reg == getWRegFromXReg(AddrReg)) { 0
447 Reg = AArch64::W9; 0
448 break; 0
449 } ----
450 } ----
451 assert(ScratchRegs[0] != AddrReg && ScratchRegs[1] != AddrReg && 0
452 "Invalid scratch registers for KCFI_CHECK"); ----
453 ----
454 // Adjust the offset for patchable-function-prefix. This assumes that ----
455 // patchable-function-prefix is the same for all functions. ----
456 int64_t PrefixNops = 0; 0
457 (void)MI.getMF() ----
458 ->getFunction() 0
459 .getFnAttribute("patchable-function-prefix") 0
460 .getValueAsString() 0
461 .getAsInteger(10, PrefixNops); 0
462 ----
463 // Load the target function type hash. ----
464 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::LDURWi) 0
465 .addReg(ScratchRegs[0]) 0
466 .addReg(AddrReg) 0
467 .addImm(-(PrefixNops * 4 + 4))); 0
468 } ----
469 ----
470 // Load the expected type hash. ----
471 const int64_t Type = MI.getOperand(1).getImm(); 0
472 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::MOVKWi) 0
473 .addReg(ScratchRegs[1]) 0
474 .addReg(ScratchRegs[1]) 0
475 .addImm(Type & 0xFFFF) 0
476 .addImm(0)); 0
477 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::MOVKWi) 0
478 .addReg(ScratchRegs[1]) 0
479 .addReg(ScratchRegs[1]) 0
480 .addImm((Type >> 16) & 0xFFFF) 0
481 .addImm(16)); 0
482 ----
483 // Compare the hashes and trap if there's a mismatch. ----
484 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::SUBSWrs) 0
485 .addReg(AArch64::WZR) 0
486 .addReg(ScratchRegs[0]) 0
487 .addReg(ScratchRegs[1]) 0
488 .addImm(0)); 0
489 ----
490 MCSymbol *Pass = OutContext.createTempSymbol(); 0
491 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, 0
492 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::Bcc) 0
493 .addImm(AArch64CC::EQ) 0
494 .addExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Pass, OutContext))); 0
495 ----
496 // The base ESR is 0x8000 and the register information is encoded in bits ----
497 // 0-9 as follows: ----
498 // - 0-4: n, where the register Xn contains the target address ----
499 // - 5-9: m, where the register Wm contains the expected type hash ----
500 // Where n, m are in [0, 30]. ----
501 unsigned TypeIndex = ScratchRegs[1] - AArch64::W0; 0
502 unsigned AddrIndex; ----
503 switch (AddrReg) { 0
504 default: 0
505 AddrIndex = AddrReg - AArch64::X0; 0
506 break; 0
507 case AArch64::FP: 0
508 AddrIndex = 29; 0
509 break; 0
510 case AArch64::LR: 0
511 AddrIndex = 30; 0
512 break; 0
513 } ----
514 ----
515 assert(AddrIndex < 31 && TypeIndex < 31); 0
516 ----
517 unsigned ESR = 0x8000 | ((TypeIndex & 31) << 5) | (AddrIndex & 31); 0
518 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::BRK).addImm(ESR)); 0
519 OutStreamer->emitLabel(Pass); 0
520 } 0
521 ----
522 void AArch64AsmPrinter::LowerHWASAN_CHECK_MEMACCESS(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
523 Register Reg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
524 bool IsShort = ----
525 MI.getOpcode() == AArch64::HWASAN_CHECK_MEMACCESS_SHORTGRANULES; 0
526 uint32_t AccessInfo = MI.getOperand(1).getImm(); 0
527 MCSymbol *&Sym = ----
528 HwasanMemaccessSymbols[HwasanMemaccessTuple(Reg, IsShort, AccessInfo)]; 0
529 if (!Sym) { 0
530 // FIXME: Make this work on non-ELF. ----
531 if (!TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatELF()) 0
532 report_fatal_error("llvm.hwasan.check.memaccess only supported on ELF"); 0
533 ----
534 std::string SymName = "__hwasan_check_x" + utostr(Reg - AArch64::X0) + "_" + 0
535 utostr(AccessInfo); 0
536 if (IsShort) 0
537 SymName += "_short_v2"; 0
538 Sym = OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol(SymName); 0
539 } 0
540 ----
541 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, 0
542 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::BL) 0
543 .addExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, OutContext))); 0
544 } 0
545 ----
546 void AArch64AsmPrinter::emitHwasanMemaccessSymbols(Module &M) { 0
547 if (HwasanMemaccessSymbols.empty()) 0
548 return; 0
549 ----
550 const Triple &TT = TM.getTargetTriple(); 0
551 assert(TT.isOSBinFormatELF()); 0
552 std::unique_ptr STI( ----
553 TM.getTarget().createMCSubtargetInfo(TT.str(), "", "")); 0
554 assert(STI && "Unable to create subtarget info"); 0
555 ----
556 MCSymbol *HwasanTagMismatchV1Sym = ----
557 OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol("__hwasan_tag_mismatch"); 0
558 MCSymbol *HwasanTagMismatchV2Sym = ----
559 OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol("__hwasan_tag_mismatch_v2"); 0
560 ----
561 const MCSymbolRefExpr *HwasanTagMismatchV1Ref = ----
562 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(HwasanTagMismatchV1Sym, OutContext); 0
563 const MCSymbolRefExpr *HwasanTagMismatchV2Ref = ----
564 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(HwasanTagMismatchV2Sym, OutContext); 0
565 ----
566 for (auto &P : HwasanMemaccessSymbols) { 0
567 unsigned Reg = std::get<0>(P.first); 0
568 bool IsShort = std::get<1>(P.first); 0
569 uint32_t AccessInfo = std::get<2>(P.first); 0
570 const MCSymbolRefExpr *HwasanTagMismatchRef = 0
571 IsShort ? HwasanTagMismatchV2Ref : HwasanTagMismatchV1Ref; 0
572 MCSymbol *Sym = P.second; 0
573 ----
574 bool HasMatchAllTag = 0
575 (AccessInfo >> HWASanAccessInfo::HasMatchAllShift) & 1; 0
576 uint8_t MatchAllTag = 0
577 (AccessInfo >> HWASanAccessInfo::MatchAllShift) & 0xff; 0
578 unsigned Size = 0
579 1 << ((AccessInfo >> HWASanAccessInfo::AccessSizeShift) & 0xf); 0
580 bool CompileKernel = 0
581 (AccessInfo >> HWASanAccessInfo::CompileKernelShift) & 1; 0
582 ----
583 OutStreamer->switchSection(OutContext.getELFSection( 0
584 ".text.hot", ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, ----
585 ELF::SHF_EXECINSTR | ELF::SHF_ALLOC | ELF::SHF_GROUP, 0, Sym->getName(), 0
586 /*IsComdat=*/true)); ----
587 ----
588 OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(Sym, MCSA_ELF_TypeFunction); 0
589 OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(Sym, MCSA_Weak); 0
590 OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(Sym, MCSA_Hidden); 0
591 OutStreamer->emitLabel(Sym); 0
592 ----
593 OutStreamer->emitInstruction(MCInstBuilder(AArch64::SBFMXri) 0
594 .addReg(AArch64::X16) 0
595 .addReg(Reg) 0
596 .addImm(4) 0
597 .addImm(55), 0
598 *STI); 0
599 OutStreamer->emitInstruction( 0
600 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::LDRBBroX) 0
601 .addReg(AArch64::W16) 0
602 .addReg(IsShort ? AArch64::X20 : AArch64::X9) 0
603 .addReg(AArch64::X16) 0
604 .addImm(0) 0
605 .addImm(0), 0
606 *STI); 0
607 OutStreamer->emitInstruction( 0
608 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::SUBSXrs) 0
609 .addReg(AArch64::XZR) 0
610 .addReg(AArch64::X16) 0
611 .addReg(Reg) 0
612 .addImm(AArch64_AM::getShifterImm(AArch64_AM::LSR, 56)), 0
613 *STI); 0
614 MCSymbol *HandleMismatchOrPartialSym = OutContext.createTempSymbol(); 0
615 OutStreamer->emitInstruction( 0
616 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::Bcc) 0
617 .addImm(AArch64CC::NE) 0
618 .addExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(HandleMismatchOrPartialSym, 0
619 OutContext)), ----
620 *STI); 0
621 MCSymbol *ReturnSym = OutContext.createTempSymbol(); 0
622 OutStreamer->emitLabel(ReturnSym); 0
623 OutStreamer->emitInstruction( 0
624 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::RET).addReg(AArch64::LR), *STI); 0
625 OutStreamer->emitLabel(HandleMismatchOrPartialSym); 0
626 ----
627 if (HasMatchAllTag) { 0
628 OutStreamer->emitInstruction(MCInstBuilder(AArch64::UBFMXri) 0
629 .addReg(AArch64::X17) 0
630 .addReg(Reg) 0
631 .addImm(56) 0
632 .addImm(63), 0
633 *STI); 0
634 OutStreamer->emitInstruction(MCInstBuilder(AArch64::SUBSXri) 0
635 .addReg(AArch64::XZR) 0
636 .addReg(AArch64::X17) 0
637 .addImm(MatchAllTag) 0
638 .addImm(0), 0
639 *STI); 0
640 OutStreamer->emitInstruction( 0
641 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::Bcc) 0
642 .addImm(AArch64CC::EQ) 0
643 .addExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(ReturnSym, OutContext)), 0
644 *STI); 0
645 } ----
646 ----
647 if (IsShort) { 0
648 OutStreamer->emitInstruction(MCInstBuilder(AArch64::SUBSWri) 0
649 .addReg(AArch64::WZR) 0
650 .addReg(AArch64::W16) 0
651 .addImm(15) 0
652 .addImm(0), 0
653 *STI); 0
654 MCSymbol *HandleMismatchSym = OutContext.createTempSymbol(); 0
655 OutStreamer->emitInstruction( 0
656 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::Bcc) 0
657 .addImm(AArch64CC::HI) 0
658 .addExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(HandleMismatchSym, OutContext)), 0
659 *STI); 0
660 ----
661 OutStreamer->emitInstruction( 0
662 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::ANDXri) 0
663 .addReg(AArch64::X17) 0
664 .addReg(Reg) 0
665 .addImm(AArch64_AM::encodeLogicalImmediate(0xf, 64)), 0
666 *STI); 0
667 if (Size != 1) 0
668 OutStreamer->emitInstruction(MCInstBuilder(AArch64::ADDXri) 0
669 .addReg(AArch64::X17) 0
670 .addReg(AArch64::X17) 0
671 .addImm(Size - 1) 0
672 .addImm(0), 0
673 *STI); 0
674 OutStreamer->emitInstruction(MCInstBuilder(AArch64::SUBSWrs) 0
675 .addReg(AArch64::WZR) 0
676 .addReg(AArch64::W16) 0
677 .addReg(AArch64::W17) 0
678 .addImm(0), 0
679 *STI); 0
680 OutStreamer->emitInstruction( 0
681 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::Bcc) 0
682 .addImm(AArch64CC::LS) 0
683 .addExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(HandleMismatchSym, OutContext)), 0
684 *STI); 0
685 ----
686 OutStreamer->emitInstruction( 0
687 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::ORRXri) 0
688 .addReg(AArch64::X16) 0
689 .addReg(Reg) 0
690 .addImm(AArch64_AM::encodeLogicalImmediate(0xf, 64)), 0
691 *STI); 0
692 OutStreamer->emitInstruction(MCInstBuilder(AArch64::LDRBBui) 0
693 .addReg(AArch64::W16) 0
694 .addReg(AArch64::X16) 0
695 .addImm(0), 0
696 *STI); 0
697 OutStreamer->emitInstruction( 0
698 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::SUBSXrs) 0
699 .addReg(AArch64::XZR) 0
700 .addReg(AArch64::X16) 0
701 .addReg(Reg) 0
702 .addImm(AArch64_AM::getShifterImm(AArch64_AM::LSR, 56)), 0
703 *STI); 0
704 OutStreamer->emitInstruction( 0
705 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::Bcc) 0
706 .addImm(AArch64CC::EQ) 0
707 .addExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(ReturnSym, OutContext)), 0
708 *STI); 0
709 ----
710 OutStreamer->emitLabel(HandleMismatchSym); 0
711 } ----
712 ----
713 OutStreamer->emitInstruction(MCInstBuilder(AArch64::STPXpre) 0
714 .addReg(AArch64::SP) 0
715 .addReg(AArch64::X0) 0
716 .addReg(AArch64::X1) 0
717 .addReg(AArch64::SP) 0
718 .addImm(-32), 0
719 *STI); 0
720 OutStreamer->emitInstruction(MCInstBuilder(AArch64::STPXi) 0
721 .addReg(AArch64::FP) 0
722 .addReg(AArch64::LR) 0
723 .addReg(AArch64::SP) 0
724 .addImm(29), 0
725 *STI); 0
726 ----
727 if (Reg != AArch64::X0) 0
728 OutStreamer->emitInstruction(MCInstBuilder(AArch64::ORRXrs) 0
729 .addReg(AArch64::X0) 0
730 .addReg(AArch64::XZR) 0
731 .addReg(Reg) 0
732 .addImm(0), 0
733 *STI); 0
734 OutStreamer->emitInstruction( 0
735 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::MOVZXi) 0
736 .addReg(AArch64::X1) 0
737 .addImm(AccessInfo & HWASanAccessInfo::RuntimeMask) 0
738 .addImm(0), 0
739 *STI); 0
740 ----
741 if (CompileKernel) { 0
742 // The Linux kernel's dynamic loader doesn't support GOT relative ----
743 // relocations, but it doesn't support late binding either, so just call ----
744 // the function directly. ----
745 OutStreamer->emitInstruction( 0
746 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::B).addExpr(HwasanTagMismatchRef), *STI); 0
747 } else { ----
748 // Intentionally load the GOT entry and branch to it, rather than possibly ----
749 // late binding the function, which may clobber the registers before we ----
750 // have a chance to save them. ----
751 OutStreamer->emitInstruction( 0
752 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::ADRP) 0
753 .addReg(AArch64::X16) 0
754 .addExpr(AArch64MCExpr::create( 0
755 HwasanTagMismatchRef, AArch64MCExpr::VariantKind::VK_GOT_PAGE, ----
756 OutContext)), ----
757 *STI); 0
758 OutStreamer->emitInstruction( 0
759 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::LDRXui) 0
760 .addReg(AArch64::X16) 0
761 .addReg(AArch64::X16) 0
762 .addExpr(AArch64MCExpr::create( 0
763 HwasanTagMismatchRef, AArch64MCExpr::VariantKind::VK_GOT_LO12, ----
764 OutContext)), ----
765 *STI); 0
766 OutStreamer->emitInstruction( 0
767 MCInstBuilder(AArch64::BR).addReg(AArch64::X16), *STI); 0
768 } ----
769 } ----
770 } 0
771 ----
772 void AArch64AsmPrinter::emitEndOfAsmFile(Module &M) { 0
773 emitHwasanMemaccessSymbols(M); 0
774 ----
775 const Triple &TT = TM.getTargetTriple(); 0
776 if (TT.isOSBinFormatMachO()) { 0
777 // Funny Darwin hack: This flag tells the linker that no global symbols ----
778 // contain code that falls through to other global symbols (e.g. the obvious ----
779 // implementation of multiple entry points). If this doesn't occur, the ----
780 // linker can safely perform dead code stripping. Since LLVM never ----
781 // generates code that does this, it is always safe to set. ----
782 OutStreamer->emitAssemblerFlag(MCAF_SubsectionsViaSymbols); 0
783 } ----
784 ----
785 // Emit stack and fault map information. ----
786 FM.serializeToFaultMapSection(); 0
787 ----
788 } 0
789 ----
790 void AArch64AsmPrinter::emitLOHs() { 0
791 SmallVector MCArgs; 0
792 ----
793 for (const auto &D : AArch64FI->getLOHContainer()) { 0
794 for (const MachineInstr *MI : D.getArgs()) { 0
795 MInstToMCSymbol::iterator LabelIt = LOHInstToLabel.find(MI); 0
796 assert(LabelIt != LOHInstToLabel.end() && 0
797 "Label hasn't been inserted for LOH related instruction"); ----
798 MCArgs.push_back(LabelIt->second); 0
799 } ----
800 OutStreamer->emitLOHDirective(D.getKind(), MCArgs); 0
801 MCArgs.clear(); 0
802 } ----
803 } 0
804 ----
805 void AArch64AsmPrinter::emitFunctionBodyEnd() { 0
806 if (!AArch64FI->getLOHRelated().empty()) 0
807 emitLOHs(); 0
808 } 0

810 /// GetCPISymbol - Return the symbol for the specified constant pool entry. ----
811 MCSymbol *AArch64AsmPrinter::GetCPISymbol(unsigned CPID) const { 0
812 // Darwin uses a linker-private symbol name for constant-pools (to ----
813 // avoid addends on the relocation?), ELF has no such concept and ----
814 // uses a normal private symbol. ----
815 if (!getDataLayout().getLinkerPrivateGlobalPrefix().empty()) 0
816 return OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol( 0
817 Twine(getDataLayout().getLinkerPrivateGlobalPrefix()) + "CPI" + 0
818 Twine(getFunctionNumber()) + "_" + Twine(CPID)); 0
819 ----
820 return AsmPrinter::GetCPISymbol(CPID); 0
821 } ----
822 ----
823 void AArch64AsmPrinter::printOperand(const MachineInstr *MI, unsigned OpNum, 0
824 raw_ostream &O) { ----
825 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(OpNum); 0
826 switch (MO.getType()) { 0
827 default: 0
828 llvm_unreachable(""); 0
829 case MachineOperand::MO_Register: { 0
830 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
831 assert(Reg.isPhysical()); 0
832 assert(!MO.getSubReg() && "Subregs should be eliminated!"); 0
833 O << AArch64InstPrinter::getRegisterName(Reg); 0
834 break; 0
835 } ----
836 case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate: { 0
837 O << MO.getImm(); 0
838 break; 0
839 } ----
840 case MachineOperand::MO_GlobalAddress: { 0
841 PrintSymbolOperand(MO, O); 0
842 break; 0
843 } ----
844 case MachineOperand::MO_BlockAddress: { 0
845 MCSymbol *Sym = GetBlockAddressSymbol(MO.getBlockAddress()); 0
846 Sym->print(O, MAI); 0
847 break; 0
848 } ----
849 } ----
850 } 0
851 ----
852 bool AArch64AsmPrinter::printAsmMRegister(const MachineOperand &MO, char Mode, 0
853 raw_ostream &O) { ----
854 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
855 switch (Mode) { 0
856 default: 0
857 return true; // Unknown mode. 0
858 case 'w': 0
859 Reg = getWRegFromXReg(Reg); 0
860 break; 0
861 case 'x': 0
862 Reg = getXRegFromWReg(Reg); 0
863 break; 0
864 case 't': 0
865 Reg = getXRegFromXRegTuple(Reg); 0
866 break; 0
867 } ----
868 ----
869 O << AArch64InstPrinter::getRegisterName(Reg); 0
870 return false; 0
871 } ----
872 ----
873 // Prints the register in MO using class RC using the offset in the ----
874 // new register class. This should not be used for cross class ----
875 // printing. ----
876 bool AArch64AsmPrinter::printAsmRegInClass(const MachineOperand &MO, 0
877 const TargetRegisterClass *RC, ----
878 unsigned AltName, raw_ostream &O) { ----
879 assert(MO.isReg() && "Should only get here with a register!"); 0
880 const TargetRegisterInfo *RI = STI->getRegisterInfo(); 0
881 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
882 unsigned RegToPrint = RC->getRegister(RI->getEncodingValue(Reg)); 0
883 if (!RI->regsOverlap(RegToPrint, Reg)) 0
884 return true; 0
885 O << AArch64InstPrinter::getRegisterName(RegToPrint, AltName); 0
886 return false; 0
887 } ----
888 ----
889 bool AArch64AsmPrinter::PrintAsmOperand(const MachineInstr *MI, unsigned OpNum, 0
890 const char *ExtraCode, raw_ostream &O) { ----
891 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(OpNum); 0
892 ----
893 // First try the generic code, which knows about modifiers like 'c' and 'n'. ----
894 if (!AsmPrinter::PrintAsmOperand(MI, OpNum, ExtraCode, O)) 0
895 return false; 0
896 ----
897 // Does this asm operand have a single letter operand modifier? ----
898 if (ExtraCode && ExtraCode[0]) { 0
899 if (ExtraCode[1] != 0) 0
900 return true; // Unknown modifier. 0
901 ----
902 switch (ExtraCode[0]) { 0
903 default: 0
904 return true; // Unknown modifier. 0
905 case 'w': // Print W register 0
906 case 'x': // Print X register ----
907 if (MO.isReg()) 0
908 return printAsmMRegister(MO, ExtraCode[0], O); 0
909 if (MO.isImm() && MO.getImm() == 0) { 0
910 unsigned Reg = ExtraCode[0] == 'w' ? AArch64::WZR : AArch64::XZR; 0
911 O << AArch64InstPrinter::getRegisterName(Reg); 0
912 return false; 0
913 } ----
914 printOperand(MI, OpNum, O); 0
915 return false; 0
916 case 'b': // Print B register. 0
917 case 'h': // Print H register. ----
918 case 's': // Print S register. ----
919 case 'd': // Print D register. ----
920 case 'q': // Print Q register. ----
921 case 'z': // Print Z register. ----
922 if (MO.isReg()) { 0
923 const TargetRegisterClass *RC; ----
924 switch (ExtraCode[0]) { 0
925 case 'b': 0
926 RC = &AArch64::FPR8RegClass; 0
927 break; 0
928 case 'h': 0
929 RC = &AArch64::FPR16RegClass; 0
930 break; 0
931 case 's': 0
932 RC = &AArch64::FPR32RegClass; 0
933 break; 0
934 case 'd': 0
935 RC = &AArch64::FPR64RegClass; 0
936 break; 0
937 case 'q': 0
938 RC = &AArch64::FPR128RegClass; 0
939 break; 0
940 case 'z': 0
941 RC = &AArch64::ZPRRegClass; 0
942 break; 0
943 default: 0
944 return true; 0
945 } ----
946 return printAsmRegInClass(MO, RC, AArch64::NoRegAltName, O); 0
947 } ----
948 printOperand(MI, OpNum, O); 0
949 return false; 0
950 } ----
951 } ----
952 ----
953 // According to ARM, we should emit x and v registers unless we have a ----
954 // modifier. ----
955 if (MO.isReg()) { 0
956 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
957 ----
958 // If this is a w or x register, print an x register. ----
959 if (AArch64::GPR32allRegClass.contains(Reg) || 0
960 AArch64::GPR64allRegClass.contains(Reg)) 0
961 return printAsmMRegister(MO, 'x', O); 0
962 ----
963 // If this is an x register tuple, print an x register. ----
964 if (AArch64::GPR64x8ClassRegClass.contains(Reg)) 0
965 return printAsmMRegister(MO, 't', O); 0
966 ----
967 unsigned AltName = AArch64::NoRegAltName; 0
968 const TargetRegisterClass *RegClass; ----
969 if (AArch64::ZPRRegClass.contains(Reg)) { 0
970 RegClass = &AArch64::ZPRRegClass; 0
971 } else if (AArch64::PPRRegClass.contains(Reg)) { 0
972 RegClass = &AArch64::PPRRegClass; 0
973 } else { ----
974 RegClass = &AArch64::FPR128RegClass; 0
975 AltName = AArch64::vreg; 0
976 } ----
977 ----
978 // If this is a b, h, s, d, or q register, print it as a v register. ----
979 return printAsmRegInClass(MO, RegClass, AltName, O); 0
980 } ----
981 ----
982 printOperand(MI, OpNum, O); 0
983 return false; 0
984 } ----
985 ----
986 bool AArch64AsmPrinter::PrintAsmMemoryOperand(const MachineInstr *MI, 0
987 unsigned OpNum, ----
988 const char *ExtraCode, ----
989 raw_ostream &O) { ----
990 if (ExtraCode && ExtraCode[0] && ExtraCode[0] != 'a') 0
991 return true; // Unknown modifier. 0
992 ----
993 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(OpNum); 0
994 assert(MO.isReg() && "unexpected inline asm memory operand"); 0
995 O << "[" << AArch64InstPrinter::getRegisterName(MO.getReg()) << "]"; 0
996 return false; 0
997 } ----
998 ----
999 void AArch64AsmPrinter::PrintDebugValueComment(const MachineInstr *MI, 0
1000 raw_ostream &OS) { ----
1001 unsigned NOps = MI->getNumOperands(); 0
1002 assert(NOps == 4); 0
1003 OS << '\t' << MAI->getCommentString() << "DEBUG_VALUE: "; 0
1004 // cast away const; DIetc do not take const operands for some reason. ----
1005 OS << MI->getDebugVariable()->getName(); 0
1006 OS << " <- "; 0
1007 // Frame address. Currently handles register +- offset only. ----
1008 assert(MI->isIndirectDebugValue()); 0
1009 OS << '['; 0
1010 for (unsigned I = 0, E = std::distance(MI->debug_operands().begin(), 0
1011 MI->debug_operands().end()); 0
1012 I < E; ++I) { 0
1013 if (I != 0) 0
1014 OS << ", "; 0
1015 printOperand(MI, I, OS); 0
1016 } ----
1017 OS << ']'; 0
1018 OS << "+"; 0
1019 printOperand(MI, NOps - 2, OS); 0
1020 } 0
1021 ----
1022 void AArch64AsmPrinter::emitJumpTableInfo() { 0
1023 const MachineJumpTableInfo *MJTI = MF->getJumpTableInfo(); 0
1024 if (!MJTI) return; 0
1025 ----
1026 const std::vector &JT = MJTI->getJumpTables(); 0
1027 if (JT.empty()) return; 0
1028 ----
1029 const TargetLoweringObjectFile &TLOF = getObjFileLowering(); 0
1030 MCSection *ReadOnlySec = TLOF.getSectionForJumpTable(MF->getFunction(), TM); 0
1031 OutStreamer->switchSection(ReadOnlySec); 0
1032 ----
1033 auto AFI = MF->getInfo(); 0
1034 for (unsigned JTI = 0, e = JT.size(); JTI != e; ++JTI) { 0
1035 const std::vector &JTBBs = JT[JTI].MBBs; 0
1036 ----
1037 // If this jump table was deleted, ignore it. ----
1038 if (JTBBs.empty()) continue; 0
1039 ----
1040 unsigned Size = AFI->getJumpTableEntrySize(JTI); 0
1041 emitAlignment(Align(Size)); 0
1042 OutStreamer->emitLabel(GetJTISymbol(JTI)); 0
1043 ----
1044 const MCSymbol *BaseSym = AArch64FI->getJumpTableEntryPCRelSymbol(JTI); 0
1045 const MCExpr *Base = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(BaseSym, OutContext); 0
1046 ----
1047 for (auto *JTBB : JTBBs) { 0
1048 const MCExpr *Value = ----
1049 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(JTBB->getSymbol(), OutContext); 0
1050 ----
1051 // Each entry is: ----
1052 // .byte/.hword (LBB - Lbase)>>2 ----
1053 // or plain: ----
1054 // .word LBB - Lbase ----
1055 Value = MCBinaryExpr::createSub(Value, Base, OutContext); 0
1056 if (Size != 4) 0
1057 Value = MCBinaryExpr::createLShr( 0
1058 Value, MCConstantExpr::create(2, OutContext), OutContext); 0
1059 ----
1060 OutStreamer->emitValue(Value, Size); 0
1061 } ----
1062 } ----
1063 } ----
1064 ----
1065 void AArch64AsmPrinter::emitFunctionEntryLabel() { 0
1066 if (MF->getFunction().getCallingConv() == CallingConv::AArch64_VectorCall || 0
1067 MF->getFunction().getCallingConv() == 0
1068 CallingConv::AArch64_SVE_VectorCall || 0
1069 MF->getInfo()->isSVECC()) { 0
1070 auto *TS = ----
1071 static_cast(OutStreamer->getTargetStreamer()); 0
1072 TS->emitDirectiveVariantPCS(CurrentFnSym); 0
1073 } ----
1074 ----
1075 return AsmPrinter::emitFunctionEntryLabel(); 0
1076 } ----
1077 ----
1078 /// Small jump tables contain an unsigned byte or half, representing the offset ----
1079 /// from the lowest-addressed possible destination to the desired basic ----
1080 /// block. Since all instructions are 4-byte aligned, this is further compressed ----
1081 /// by counting in instructions rather than bytes (i.e. divided by 4). So, to ----
1082 /// materialize the correct destination we need: ----
1083 /// ----
1084 /// adr xDest, .LBB0_0 ----
1085 /// ldrb wScratch, [xTable, xEntry] (with "lsl #1" for ldrh). ----
1086 /// add xDest, xDest, xScratch (with "lsl #2" for smaller entries) ----
1087 void AArch64AsmPrinter::LowerJumpTableDest(llvm::MCStreamer &OutStreamer, 0
1088 const llvm::MachineInstr &MI) { ----
1089 Register DestReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1090 Register ScratchReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1091 Register ScratchRegW = ----
1092 STI->getRegisterInfo()->getSubReg(ScratchReg, AArch64::sub_32); 0
1093 Register TableReg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
1094 Register EntryReg = MI.getOperand(3).getReg(); 0
1095 int JTIdx = MI.getOperand(4).getIndex(); 0
1096 int Size = AArch64FI->getJumpTableEntrySize(JTIdx); 0
1097 ----
1098 // This has to be first because the compression pass based its reachability ----
1099 // calculations on the start of the JumpTableDest instruction. ----
1100 auto Label = ----
1101 MF->getInfo()->getJumpTableEntryPCRelSymbol(JTIdx); 0
1102 ----
1103 // If we don't already have a symbol to use as the base, use the ADR ----
1104 // instruction itself. ----
1105 if (!Label) { 0
1106 Label = MF->getContext().createTempSymbol(); 0
1107 AArch64FI->setJumpTableEntryInfo(JTIdx, Size, Label); 0
1108 OutStreamer.emitLabel(Label); 0
1109 } ----
1110 ----
1111 auto LabelExpr = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Label, MF->getContext()); 0
1112 EmitToStreamer(OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::ADR) 0
1113 .addReg(DestReg) 0
1114 .addExpr(LabelExpr)); 0
1115 ----
1116 // Load the number of instruction-steps to offset from the label. ----
1117 unsigned LdrOpcode; ----
1118 switch (Size) { 0
1119 case 1: LdrOpcode = AArch64::LDRBBroX; break; 0
1120 case 2: LdrOpcode = AArch64::LDRHHroX; break; 0
1121 case 4: LdrOpcode = AArch64::LDRSWroX; break; 0
1122 default: 0
1123 llvm_unreachable("Unknown jump table size"); 0
1124 } ----
1125 ----
1126 EmitToStreamer(OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(LdrOpcode) 0
1127 .addReg(Size == 4 ? ScratchReg : ScratchRegW) 0
1128 .addReg(TableReg) 0
1129 .addReg(EntryReg) 0
1130 .addImm(0) 0
1131 .addImm(Size == 1 ? 0 : 1)); 0
1132 ----
1133 // Add to the already materialized base label address, multiplying by 4 if ----
1134 // compressed. ----
1135 EmitToStreamer(OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::ADDXrs) 0
1136 .addReg(DestReg) 0
1137 .addReg(DestReg) 0
1138 .addReg(ScratchReg) 0
1139 .addImm(Size == 4 ? 0 : 2)); 0
1140 } 0
1141 ----
1142 void AArch64AsmPrinter::LowerMOPS(llvm::MCStreamer &OutStreamer, 0
1143 const llvm::MachineInstr &MI) { ----
1144 unsigned Opcode = MI.getOpcode(); 0
1145 assert(STI->hasMOPS()); 0
1146 assert(STI->hasMTE() || Opcode != AArch64::MOPSMemorySetTaggingPseudo); 0
1147 ----
1148 const auto Ops = [Opcode]() -> std::array { 0
1149 if (Opcode == AArch64::MOPSMemoryCopyPseudo) 0
1150 return {AArch64::CPYFP, AArch64::CPYFM, AArch64::CPYFE}; 0
1151 if (Opcode == AArch64::MOPSMemoryMovePseudo) 0
1152 return {AArch64::CPYP, AArch64::CPYM, AArch64::CPYE}; 0
1153 if (Opcode == AArch64::MOPSMemorySetPseudo) 0
1154 return {AArch64::SETP, AArch64::SETM, AArch64::SETE}; 0
1155 if (Opcode == AArch64::MOPSMemorySetTaggingPseudo) 0
1156 return {AArch64::SETGP, AArch64::SETGM, AArch64::MOPSSETGE}; 0
1157 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled memory operation pseudo"); 0
1158 }(); 0
1159 const bool IsSet = Opcode == AArch64::MOPSMemorySetPseudo || 0
1160 Opcode == AArch64::MOPSMemorySetTaggingPseudo; ----
1161 ----
1162 for (auto Op : Ops) { 0
1163 int i = 0; 0
1164 auto MCIB = MCInstBuilder(Op); 0
1165 // Destination registers ----
1166 MCIB.addReg(MI.getOperand(i++).getReg()); 0
1167 MCIB.addReg(MI.getOperand(i++).getReg()); 0
1168 if (!IsSet) 0
1169 MCIB.addReg(MI.getOperand(i++).getReg()); 0
1170 // Input registers ----
1171 MCIB.addReg(MI.getOperand(i++).getReg()); 0
1172 MCIB.addReg(MI.getOperand(i++).getReg()); 0
1173 MCIB.addReg(MI.getOperand(i++).getReg()); 0
1174 ----
1175 EmitToStreamer(OutStreamer, MCIB); 0
1176 } 0
1177 } 0
1178 ----
1179 void AArch64AsmPrinter::LowerSTACKMAP(MCStreamer &OutStreamer, StackMaps &SM, 0
1180 const MachineInstr &MI) { ----
1181 unsigned NumNOPBytes = StackMapOpers(&MI).getNumPatchBytes(); 0
1182 ----
1183 auto &Ctx = OutStreamer.getContext(); 0
1184 MCSymbol *MILabel = Ctx.createTempSymbol(); 0
1185 OutStreamer.emitLabel(MILabel); 0
1186 ----
1187 SM.recordStackMap(*MILabel, MI); 0
1188 assert(NumNOPBytes % 4 == 0 && "Invalid number of NOP bytes requested!"); 0
1189 ----
1190 // Scan ahead to trim the shadow. ----
1191 const MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI.getParent(); 0
1192 MachineBasicBlock::const_iterator MII(MI); 0
1193 ++MII; 0
1194 while (NumNOPBytes > 0) { 0
1195 if (MII == MBB.end() || MII->isCall() || 0
1196 MII->getOpcode() == AArch64::DBG_VALUE || 0
1197 MII->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::PATCHPOINT || 0
1198 MII->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::STACKMAP) 0
1199 break; 0
1200 ++MII; 0
1201 NumNOPBytes -= 4; 0
1202 } ----
1203 ----
1204 // Emit nops. ----
1205 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumNOPBytes; i += 4) 0
1206 EmitToStreamer(OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::HINT).addImm(0)); 0
1207 } 0
1208 ----
1209 // Lower a patchpoint of the form: ----
1210 // [], , , , ----
1211 void AArch64AsmPrinter::LowerPATCHPOINT(MCStreamer &OutStreamer, StackMaps &SM, 0
1212 const MachineInstr &MI) { ----
1213 auto &Ctx = OutStreamer.getContext(); 0
1214 MCSymbol *MILabel = Ctx.createTempSymbol(); 0
1215 OutStreamer.emitLabel(MILabel); 0
1216 SM.recordPatchPoint(*MILabel, MI); 0
1217 ----
1218 PatchPointOpers Opers(&MI); 0
1219 ----
1220 int64_t CallTarget = Opers.getCallTarget().getImm(); 0
1221 unsigned EncodedBytes = 0; 0
1222 if (CallTarget) { 0
1223 assert((CallTarget & 0xFFFFFFFFFFFF) == CallTarget && 0
1224 "High 16 bits of call target should be zero."); ----
1225 Register ScratchReg = MI.getOperand(Opers.getNextScratchIdx()).getReg(); 0
1226 EncodedBytes = 16; 0
1227 // Materialize the jump address: ----
1228 EmitToStreamer(OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::MOVZXi) 0
1229 .addReg(ScratchReg) 0
1230 .addImm((CallTarget >> 32) & 0xFFFF) 0
1231 .addImm(32)); 0
1232 EmitToStreamer(OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::MOVKXi) 0
1233 .addReg(ScratchReg) 0
1234 .addReg(ScratchReg) 0
1235 .addImm((CallTarget >> 16) & 0xFFFF) 0
1236 .addImm(16)); 0
1237 EmitToStreamer(OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::MOVKXi) 0
1238 .addReg(ScratchReg) 0
1239 .addReg(ScratchReg) 0
1240 .addImm(CallTarget & 0xFFFF) 0
1241 .addImm(0)); 0
1242 EmitToStreamer(OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::BLR).addReg(ScratchReg)); 0
1243 } ----
1244 // Emit padding. ----
1245 unsigned NumBytes = Opers.getNumPatchBytes(); 0
1246 assert(NumBytes >= EncodedBytes && 0
1247 "Patchpoint can't request size less than the length of a call."); ----
1248 assert((NumBytes - EncodedBytes) % 4 == 0 && 0
1249 "Invalid number of NOP bytes requested!"); ----
1250 for (unsigned i = EncodedBytes; i < NumBytes; i += 4) 0
1251 EmitToStreamer(OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::HINT).addImm(0)); 0
1252 } 0
1253 ----
1254 void AArch64AsmPrinter::LowerSTATEPOINT(MCStreamer &OutStreamer, StackMaps &SM, 0
1255 const MachineInstr &MI) { ----
1256 StatepointOpers SOpers(&MI); 0
1257 if (unsigned PatchBytes = SOpers.getNumPatchBytes()) { 0
1258 assert(PatchBytes % 4 == 0 && "Invalid number of NOP bytes requested!"); 0
1259 for (unsigned i = 0; i < PatchBytes; i += 4) 0
1260 EmitToStreamer(OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(AArch64::HINT).addImm(0)); 0
1261 } else { ----
1262 // Lower call target and choose correct opcode ----
1263 const MachineOperand &CallTarget = SOpers.getCallTarget(); 0
1264 MCOperand CallTargetMCOp; 0
1265 unsigned CallOpcode; ----
1266 switch (CallTarget.getType()) { 0
1267 case MachineOperand::MO_GlobalAddress: 0
1268 case MachineOperand::MO_ExternalSymbol: ----
1269 MCInstLowering.lowerOperand(CallTarget, CallTargetMCOp); 0
1270 CallOpcode = AArch64::BL; 0
1271 break; 0
1272 case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate: 0
1273 CallTargetMCOp = MCOperand::createImm(CallTarget.getImm()); 0
1274 CallOpcode = AArch64::BL; 0
1275 break; 0
1276 case MachineOperand::MO_Register: 0
1277 CallTargetMCOp = MCOperand::createReg(CallTarget.getReg()); 0
1278 CallOpcode = AArch64::BLR; 0
1279 break; 0
1280 default: 0
1281 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported operand type in statepoint call target"); 0
1282 break; ----
1283 } ----
1284 ----
1285 EmitToStreamer(OutStreamer, 0
1286 MCInstBuilder(CallOpcode).addOperand(CallTargetMCOp)); 0
1287 } ----
1288 ----
1289 auto &Ctx = OutStreamer.getContext(); 0
1290 MCSymbol *MILabel = Ctx.createTempSymbol(); 0
1291 OutStreamer.emitLabel(MILabel); 0
1292 SM.recordStatepoint(*MILabel, MI); 0
1293 } 0
1294 ----
1295 void AArch64AsmPrinter::LowerFAULTING_OP(const MachineInstr &FaultingMI) { 0
1296 // FAULTING_LOAD_OP , , , ----
1297 // , ----
1298 ----
1299 Register DefRegister = FaultingMI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1300 FaultMaps::FaultKind FK = ----
1301 static_cast(FaultingMI.getOperand(1).getImm()); 0
1302 MCSymbol *HandlerLabel = FaultingMI.getOperand(2).getMBB()->getSymbol(); 0
1303 unsigned Opcode = FaultingMI.getOperand(3).getImm(); 0
1304 unsigned OperandsBeginIdx = 4; 0
1305 ----
1306 auto &Ctx = OutStreamer->getContext(); 0
1307 MCSymbol *FaultingLabel = Ctx.createTempSymbol(); 0
1308 OutStreamer->emitLabel(FaultingLabel); 0
1309 ----
1310 assert(FK < FaultMaps::FaultKindMax && "Invalid Faulting Kind!"); 0
1311 FM.recordFaultingOp(FK, FaultingLabel, HandlerLabel); 0
1312 ----
1313 MCInst MI; 0
1314 MI.setOpcode(Opcode); 0
1315 ----
1316 if (DefRegister != (Register)0) 0
1317 MI.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(DefRegister)); 0
1318 ----
1319 for (const MachineOperand &MO : 0
1320 llvm::drop_begin(FaultingMI.operands(), OperandsBeginIdx)) { 0
1321 MCOperand Dest; 0
1322 lowerOperand(MO, Dest); 0
1323 MI.addOperand(Dest); 0
1324 } ----
1325 ----
1326 OutStreamer->AddComment("on-fault: " + HandlerLabel->getName()); 0
1327 OutStreamer->emitInstruction(MI, getSubtargetInfo()); 0
1328 } 0
1329 ----
1330 void AArch64AsmPrinter::emitFMov0(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1331 Register DestReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1332 if (STI->hasZeroCycleZeroingFP() && !STI->hasZeroCycleZeroingFPWorkaround() && 0
1333 STI->isNeonAvailable()) { 0
1334 // Convert H/S register to corresponding D register ----
1335 if (AArch64::H0 <= DestReg && DestReg <= AArch64::H31) 0
1336 DestReg = AArch64::D0 + (DestReg - AArch64::H0); 0
1337 else if (AArch64::S0 <= DestReg && DestReg <= AArch64::S31) 0
1338 DestReg = AArch64::D0 + (DestReg - AArch64::S0); 0
1339 else ----
1340 assert(AArch64::D0 <= DestReg && DestReg <= AArch64::D31); 0
1341 ----
1342 MCInst MOVI; 0
1343 MOVI.setOpcode(AArch64::MOVID); 0
1344 MOVI.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(DestReg)); 0
1345 MOVI.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0)); 0
1346 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MOVI); 0
1347 } else { 0
1348 MCInst FMov; 0
1349 switch (MI.getOpcode()) { 0
1350 default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected opcode"); 0
1351 case AArch64::FMOVH0: 0
1352 FMov.setOpcode(STI->hasFullFP16() ? AArch64::FMOVWHr : AArch64::FMOVWSr); 0
1353 if (!STI->hasFullFP16()) 0
1354 DestReg = (AArch64::S0 + (DestReg - AArch64::H0)); 0
1355 FMov.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(DestReg)); 0
1356 FMov.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AArch64::WZR)); 0
1357 break; 0
1358 case AArch64::FMOVS0: 0
1359 FMov.setOpcode(AArch64::FMOVWSr); 0
1360 FMov.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(DestReg)); 0
1361 FMov.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AArch64::WZR)); 0
1362 break; 0
1363 case AArch64::FMOVD0: 0
1364 FMov.setOpcode(AArch64::FMOVXDr); 0
1365 FMov.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(DestReg)); 0
1366 FMov.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AArch64::XZR)); 0
1367 break; 0
1368 } ----
1369 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, FMov); 0
1370 } 0
1371 } 0
1372 ----
1373 // Simple pseudo-instructions have their lowering (with expansion to real ----
1374 // instructions) auto-generated. ----
1375 #include "AArch64GenMCPseudoLowering.inc" ----
1376 ----
1377 void AArch64AsmPrinter::emitInstruction(const MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1378 AArch64_MC::verifyInstructionPredicates(MI->getOpcode(), STI->getFeatureBits()); 0
1379 ----
1380 // Do any auto-generated pseudo lowerings. ----
1381 if (emitPseudoExpansionLowering(*OutStreamer, MI)) 0
1382 return; 0
1383 ----
1384 if (MI->getOpcode() == AArch64::ADRP) { 0
1385 for (auto &Opd : MI->operands()) { 0
1386 if (Opd.isSymbol() && StringRef(Opd.getSymbolName()) == 0
1387 "swift_async_extendedFramePointerFlags") { 0
1388 ShouldEmitWeakSwiftAsyncExtendedFramePointerFlags = true; 0
1389 } ----
1390 } ----
1391 } ----
1392 ----
1393 if (AArch64FI->getLOHRelated().count(MI)) { 0
1394 // Generate a label for LOH related instruction ----
1395 MCSymbol *LOHLabel = createTempSymbol("loh"); 0
1396 // Associate the instruction with the label ----
1397 LOHInstToLabel[MI] = LOHLabel; 0
1398 OutStreamer->emitLabel(LOHLabel); 0
1399 } ----
1400 ----
1401 AArch64TargetStreamer *TS = ----
1402 static_cast(OutStreamer->getTargetStreamer()); 0
1403 // Do any manual lowerings. ----
1404 switch (MI->getOpcode()) { 0
1405 default: 0
1406 break; 0
1407 case AArch64::HINT: { 0
1408 // CurrentPatchableFunctionEntrySym can be CurrentFnBegin only for ----
1409 // -fpatchable-function-entry=N,0. The entry MBB is guaranteed to be ----
1410 // non-empty. If MI is the initial BTI, place the ----
1411 // __patchable_function_entries label after BTI. ----
1412 if (CurrentPatchableFunctionEntrySym && 0
1413 CurrentPatchableFunctionEntrySym == CurrentFnBegin && 0
1414 MI == &MF->front().front()) { 0
1415 int64_t Imm = MI->getOperand(0).getImm(); 0
1416 if ((Imm & 32) && (Imm & 6)) { 0
1417 MCInst Inst; 0
1418 MCInstLowering.Lower(MI, Inst); 0
1419 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, Inst); 0
1420 CurrentPatchableFunctionEntrySym = createTempSymbol("patch"); 0
1421 OutStreamer->emitLabel(CurrentPatchableFunctionEntrySym); 0
1422 return; 0
1423 } 0
1424 } ----
1425 break; 0
1426 } ----
1427 case AArch64::MOVMCSym: { 0
1428 Register DestReg = MI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1429 const MachineOperand &MO_Sym = MI->getOperand(1); 0
1430 MachineOperand Hi_MOSym(MO_Sym), Lo_MOSym(MO_Sym); 0
1431 MCOperand Hi_MCSym, Lo_MCSym; 0
1432 ----
1433 Hi_MOSym.setTargetFlags(AArch64II::MO_G1 | AArch64II::MO_S); 0
1434 Lo_MOSym.setTargetFlags(AArch64II::MO_G0 | AArch64II::MO_NC); 0
1435 ----
1436 MCInstLowering.lowerOperand(Hi_MOSym, Hi_MCSym); 0
1437 MCInstLowering.lowerOperand(Lo_MOSym, Lo_MCSym); 0
1438 ----
1439 MCInst MovZ; 0
1440 MovZ.setOpcode(AArch64::MOVZXi); 0
1441 MovZ.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(DestReg)); 0
1442 MovZ.addOperand(Hi_MCSym); 0
1443 MovZ.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(16)); 0
1444 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MovZ); 0
1445 ----
1446 MCInst MovK; 0
1447 MovK.setOpcode(AArch64::MOVKXi); 0
1448 MovK.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(DestReg)); 0
1449 MovK.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(DestReg)); 0
1450 MovK.addOperand(Lo_MCSym); 0
1451 MovK.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0)); 0
1452 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MovK); 0
1453 return; 0
1454 } 0
1455 case AArch64::MOVIv2d_ns: 0
1456 // If the target has , lower this ----
1457 // instruction to movi.16b instead. ----
1458 if (STI->hasZeroCycleZeroingFPWorkaround() && 0
1459 MI->getOperand(1).getImm() == 0) { 0
1460 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1461 TmpInst.setOpcode(AArch64::MOVIv16b_ns); 0
1462 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg())); 0
1463 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(MI->getOperand(1).getImm())); 0
1464 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
1465 return; 0
1466 } 0
1467 break; 0
1468 ----
1469 case AArch64::DBG_VALUE: 0
1470 case AArch64::DBG_VALUE_LIST: ----
1471 if (isVerbose() && OutStreamer->hasRawTextSupport()) { 0
1472 SmallString<128> TmpStr; 0
1473 raw_svector_ostream OS(TmpStr); 0
1474 PrintDebugValueComment(MI, OS); 0
1475 OutStreamer->emitRawText(StringRef(OS.str())); 0
1476 } 0
1477 return; 0
1478 ----
1479 case AArch64::EMITBKEY: { 0
1480 ExceptionHandling ExceptionHandlingType = MAI->getExceptionHandlingType(); 0
1481 if (ExceptionHandlingType != ExceptionHandling::DwarfCFI && 0
1482 ExceptionHandlingType != ExceptionHandling::ARM) ----
1483 return; 0
1484 ----
1485 if (getFunctionCFISectionType(*MF) == CFISection::None) 0
1486 return; 0
1487 ----
1488 OutStreamer->emitCFIBKeyFrame(); 0
1489 return; 0
1490 } ----
1491 ----
1492 case AArch64::EMITMTETAGGED: { 0
1493 ExceptionHandling ExceptionHandlingType = MAI->getExceptionHandlingType(); 0
1494 if (ExceptionHandlingType != ExceptionHandling::DwarfCFI && 0
1495 ExceptionHandlingType != ExceptionHandling::ARM) ----
1496 return; 0
1497 ----
1498 if (getFunctionCFISectionType(*MF) != CFISection::None) 0
1499 OutStreamer->emitCFIMTETaggedFrame(); 0
1500 return; 0
1501 } ----
1502 ----
1503 // Tail calls use pseudo instructions so they have the proper code-gen ----
1504 // attributes (isCall, isReturn, etc.). We lower them to the real ----
1505 // instruction here. ----
1506 case AArch64::TCRETURNri: 0
1507 case AArch64::TCRETURNriBTI: ----
1508 case AArch64::TCRETURNriALL: { ----
1509 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1510 TmpInst.setOpcode(AArch64::BR); 0
1511 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg())); 0
1512 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
1513 return; 0
1514 } 0
1515 case AArch64::TCRETURNdi: { 0
1516 MCOperand Dest; 0
1517 MCInstLowering.lowerOperand(MI->getOperand(0), Dest); 0
1518 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1519 TmpInst.setOpcode(AArch64::B); 0
1520 TmpInst.addOperand(Dest); 0
1521 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
1522 return; 0
1523 } 0
1524 case AArch64::SpeculationBarrierISBDSBEndBB: { 0
1525 // Print DSB SYS + ISB ----
1526 MCInst TmpInstDSB; 0
1527 TmpInstDSB.setOpcode(AArch64::DSB); 0
1528 TmpInstDSB.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0xf)); 0
1529 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInstDSB); 0
1530 MCInst TmpInstISB; 0
1531 TmpInstISB.setOpcode(AArch64::ISB); 0
1532 TmpInstISB.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0xf)); 0
1533 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInstISB); 0
1534 return; 0
1535 } 0
1536 case AArch64::SpeculationBarrierSBEndBB: { 0
1537 // Print SB ----
1538 MCInst TmpInstSB; 0
1539 TmpInstSB.setOpcode(AArch64::SB); 0
1540 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInstSB); 0
1541 return; 0
1542 } 0
1543 case AArch64::TLSDESC_CALLSEQ: { 0
1544 /// lower this to: ----
1545 /// adrp x0, :tlsdesc:var ----
1546 /// ldr x1, [x0, #:tlsdesc_lo12:var] ----
1547 /// add x0, x0, #:tlsdesc_lo12:var ----
1548 /// .tlsdesccall var ----
1549 /// blr x1 ----
1550 /// (TPIDR_EL0 offset now in x0) ----
1551 const MachineOperand &MO_Sym = MI->getOperand(0); 0
1552 MachineOperand MO_TLSDESC_LO12(MO_Sym), MO_TLSDESC(MO_Sym); 0
1553 MCOperand Sym, SymTLSDescLo12, SymTLSDesc; 0
1554 MO_TLSDESC_LO12.setTargetFlags(AArch64II::MO_TLS | AArch64II::MO_PAGEOFF); 0
1555 MO_TLSDESC.setTargetFlags(AArch64II::MO_TLS | AArch64II::MO_PAGE); 0
1556 MCInstLowering.lowerOperand(MO_Sym, Sym); 0
1557 MCInstLowering.lowerOperand(MO_TLSDESC_LO12, SymTLSDescLo12); 0
1558 MCInstLowering.lowerOperand(MO_TLSDESC, SymTLSDesc); 0
1559 ----
1560 MCInst Adrp; 0
1561 Adrp.setOpcode(AArch64::ADRP); 0
1562 Adrp.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AArch64::X0)); 0
1563 Adrp.addOperand(SymTLSDesc); 0
1564 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, Adrp); 0
1565 ----
1566 MCInst Ldr; 0
1567 if (STI->isTargetILP32()) { 0
1568 Ldr.setOpcode(AArch64::LDRWui); 0
1569 Ldr.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AArch64::W1)); 0
1570 } else { ----
1571 Ldr.setOpcode(AArch64::LDRXui); 0
1572 Ldr.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AArch64::X1)); 0
1573 } ----
1574 Ldr.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AArch64::X0)); 0
1575 Ldr.addOperand(SymTLSDescLo12); 0
1576 Ldr.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0)); 0
1577 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, Ldr); 0
1578 ----
1579 MCInst Add; 0
1580 if (STI->isTargetILP32()) { 0
1581 Add.setOpcode(AArch64::ADDWri); 0
1582 Add.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AArch64::W0)); 0
1583 Add.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AArch64::W0)); 0
1584 } else { ----
1585 Add.setOpcode(AArch64::ADDXri); 0
1586 Add.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AArch64::X0)); 0
1587 Add.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AArch64::X0)); 0
1588 } ----
1589 Add.addOperand(SymTLSDescLo12); 0
1590 Add.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(AArch64_AM::getShiftValue(0))); 0
1591 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, Add); 0
1592 ----
1593 // Emit a relocation-annotation. This expands to no code, but requests ----
1594 // the following instruction gets an R_AARCH64_TLSDESC_CALL. ----
1595 MCInst TLSDescCall; 0
1596 TLSDescCall.setOpcode(AArch64::TLSDESCCALL); 0
1597 TLSDescCall.addOperand(Sym); 0
1598 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TLSDescCall); 0
1599 ----
1600 MCInst Blr; 0
1601 Blr.setOpcode(AArch64::BLR); 0
1602 Blr.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AArch64::X1)); 0
1603 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, Blr); 0
1604 ----
1605 return; 0
1606 } 0
1607 ----
1608 case AArch64::JumpTableDest32: 0
1609 case AArch64::JumpTableDest16: ----
1610 case AArch64::JumpTableDest8: ----
1611 LowerJumpTableDest(*OutStreamer, *MI); 0
1612 return; 0
1613 ----
1614 case AArch64::FMOVH0: 0
1615 case AArch64::FMOVS0: ----
1616 case AArch64::FMOVD0: ----
1617 emitFMov0(*MI); 0
1618 return; 0
1619 ----
1620 case AArch64::MOPSMemoryCopyPseudo: 0
1621 case AArch64::MOPSMemoryMovePseudo: ----
1622 case AArch64::MOPSMemorySetPseudo: ----
1623 case AArch64::MOPSMemorySetTaggingPseudo: ----
1624 LowerMOPS(*OutStreamer, *MI); 0
1625 return; 0
1626 ----
1627 case TargetOpcode::STACKMAP: 0
1628 return LowerSTACKMAP(*OutStreamer, SM, *MI); 0
1629 ----
1630 case TargetOpcode::PATCHPOINT: 0
1631 return LowerPATCHPOINT(*OutStreamer, SM, *MI); 0
1632 ----
1633 case TargetOpcode::STATEPOINT: 0
1634 return LowerSTATEPOINT(*OutStreamer, SM, *MI); 0
1635 ----
1636 case TargetOpcode::FAULTING_OP: 0
1637 return LowerFAULTING_OP(*MI); 0
1638 ----
1639 case TargetOpcode::PATCHABLE_FUNCTION_ENTER: 0
1640 LowerPATCHABLE_FUNCTION_ENTER(*MI); 0
1641 return; 0
1642 ----
1643 case TargetOpcode::PATCHABLE_FUNCTION_EXIT: 0
1644 LowerPATCHABLE_FUNCTION_EXIT(*MI); 0
